Standard options:
-e: select all processes
-f: full format listing

BSD options:
a: show process of other users
x: show process which don't have a tty
u: display user-oriented format
T: show processes associated to this terminal
   ['ps' is a shortcut for 'ps T'; this explains why 'ps u' show user
   informations of all processes that have a tty, and 'ps ut' gives the
   user information of the processes shown by 'ps' ]

Default: PID TTY          TIME CMD
-f       UID        PID  PPID  C STIME TTY          TIME CMD
u        USER       PID %CPU %MEM    VSZ   RSS TTY      STAT START   TIME COMMAND
